cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a deep learning method for content-aware image retargeting, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The method uses a convolutional neural network (CNN) for learning the mapping between source and target images, which falls under the category of multimedia (MM) processing. Hence, cs.MM is also a likely sub-category. The network is trained in a weakly- and self-supervised manner, which involves techniques such as reinforcement learning and unsupervised learning, falling under the categories of ML (cs.LG) and AI (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method in terms of preserving image content and structure, which involves graphics (cs.GR) techniques.
